            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1355257623,
            "creation_date": 1355257221,
            "body": "<p>I believe what you wrote is the signature of the method you have to create.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public void printReverse(char[] letters, int size){\n   //code here\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You would have to iterate the array and print what it contains backwards. Use a reverse \"for loop\" to go through each item in \"letters\". I'll let you combine these yourself as it's an assignment. Here's an example of a for loop:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>for (int i = array.length-1; i &gt;= 0 ; i--){\n    System.out.print(array[i]);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 13827862,
            "question_id": 13827654,
            "last_edit_date": 1355257623
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/100000647770651/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 3765197,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3128894,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3128894/prodigy",
                "reputation": 380,
                "display_name": "Prodigy",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1560143751,
            "creation_date": 1560143751,
            "body": "<p>This should take about 6 ms.\nIt reverses a char array \"in-place\" before printing.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void reverseString(char[] s) {\n    int len = s.length;\n\n    if (len == 0)\n        return;\n\n    for (int i=0; i &lt; (len/2); i++)\n    {\n        char l = s[i];\n        s[i] = s[len-i-1];\n        s[len-i-1] = l;\n    }\n\n    System.out.println(s);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 56520830,
            "question_id": 13827654
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/153128328352933/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 6721216,
                "user_type": "registered",
